When attempting to use the section / column macros to format information on a page in a centered fashion with dynamic width side columns (the center column is fixed width), the spacing of the columns is off if a border isn't used with the section.

To demonstrate the issue, use these macros for a page setup:

{noformat}
{section}
{column}
{column}
{column:width=800px}
{center}
{loremipsum}
{center}
{column}
{column}
{column}
{section}
{noformat}

You will see that the example text isn't centered on the page.  However, if you add a border to the section, it becomes centered.  This same code worked fine in 3.5.x.  A support request was filed (CSP-84515) where the issue was able to be replicated by the technician.

I have attached pictures showing the outcome with and without borders.

